oc=Perseus%3Atext%3A2002.02.0006%3Asura%3D21%3Averse%3D87" about="#mwt570" id="mwBBo">21:87–88</a></span></li><li about="#cite_note-107" id="cite_note-107"><a href="./Anger#cite_ref-107" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-107" class="mw-reference-text"><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Quran" title="Quran" about="#mwt573" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"cite quran","href":"./Template:Cite_quran"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"9"},"2":{"wt":"15"},"s":{"wt":"ns"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwBBs">Quran</a><span typeof="mw:Entity" about="#mwt573" id="mwBBw"> </span><a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="http://www.perseus.tufts.edu/hopper/text?doc=Perseus%3Atext%3A2002.02.0006%3Asura%3D9%3Averse%3D15" about="#mwt573" id="mwBB0">9:15</a></span></li><li about="#cite_note-AngerQ-108" id="cite_note-AngerQ-108"><span rel="mw:referencedBy"><a href="./Anger#cite_ref-AngerQ_108-0"><span class="mw-linkback-text">1 </span></a><a href="./Anger#cite_ref-AngerQ_108-1"><span class="mw-linkback-text">2 </span></a></span> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-AngerQ-108" class="mw-reference-text">Bashir, Shahzad. <i id="mwBB4">Anger</i>, <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Encyclopaedia_of_the_Qur'an" title="Encyclopaedia of the Qur'an" id="mwBB8" class="mw-redirect">Encyclopaedia of the Qur'an</a>, Brill, 2007.</span></li><li about="#cite_note-109" id="cite_note-109"><a href="./Anger#cite_ref-109" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-109" class="mw-reference-text"><i about="#mwt574" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"hadith-usc","href":"./Template:Hadith-usc"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"bukhari"},"2":{"wt":"8"},"3":{"wt":"73"},"4":{"wt":"135"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwBCA"><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Sahih_al-Bukhari" title="Sahih al-Bukhari" id="mwBCE">Sahih al-Bukhari</a></i><span about="#mwt574" id="mwBCI">, </span><a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="http://cmje.usc.edu/religious-texts/hadith/bukhari/073-sbt.php#008.073.135" about="#mwt574" id="mwBCM">8:73:135</a></span></li><li about="#cite_note-110" id="cite_note-110"><a href="./Anger#cite_ref-110" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-110" class="mw-reference-text">Mohammed Abu-Nimer, <i id="mwBCQ">Non-Violence, Peacebuilding, Conflict Resolution and Human Rights in Islam:A Framework for Nonviolence and Peacebuilding in Islam</i>, Journal of Law and Religion, Vol. 15, No. 1/2. (2000–2001), pp. 217–265.</span></li><li about="#cite_note-DictionaryofR-111" id="cite_note-DictionaryofR-111"><span rel="mw:referencedBy"><a href="./Anger#cite_ref-DictionaryofR_111-0"><span class="mw-linkback-text">1 </span></a><a href="./Anger#cite_ref-DictionaryofR_111-1"><span class="mw-linkback-text">2 </span></a><a href="./Anger#cite_ref-DictionaryofR_111-2"><span class="mw-linkback-text">3 </span></a></span> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-DictionaryofR-111" class="mw-reference-text">Shailer Mathews, Gerald Birney Smith, A Dictionary of Religion and Ethics, Kessinger Publishing, p.17</span></li></ol></div></div>

